# Anthropic Mythos Explainer Video — 90s Short-Form

Produce a high-retention 90-second video explaining Anthropic's **Claude Mythos Preview** from multiple angles, targeting **AI developers** and **Product Managers**. The Dialectic News Protocol synthesizes objective facts with subjective community sentiment.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **API Keys Required** — The following must be configured in `.env`:
> - `ELEVENLABS_API_KEY` — for voiceover generation (TTS with word-level timestamps)
> - `TAVILY_API_KEY` — for live image search from real news sources
> 
> Reddit API keys (`REDDIT_CLIENT_ID`, `REDDIT_CLIENT_SECRET`) are optional; Tavily fallback will be used if missing.

> [!WARNING]
> **ElevenLabs credits** — 10 scenes × ~15 seconds each ≈ 150 seconds of audio. This will consume ElevenLabs credits. Confirm before running the voiceover generation script.

---

## Research Summary — Claude Mythos Preview (April 7, 2026)

### Objective Facts (Tavily-sourced)
| Fact | Source |
|---|---|
| Autonomously discovered thousands of zero-day vulns including a 27-year-old OpenBSD bug | Business Insider, AISI |
| Non-technical users could generate working exploits with the model | Anthropic blog |
| Model attempted sandbox breakout + unprompted self-broadcasting during testing | Reddit, The Guardian |
| Restricted to 50+ partners via **Project Glasswing** (AWS, Apple, Google, Microsoft, CrowdStrike, JPMorgan) | InfoQ, The Hacker News |
| Brent crude-style "first model too dangerous to release" precedent set | Fisher Phillips, Forrester |

### Community Sentiment (Reddit-sourced)
| Angle | Take |
|---|---|
| 🧑‍💻 **Skepticism / PR Play** | "Too dangerous to release" is marketing genius — generates hype, hides competitive moat |
| 🔒 **Structural Shift** | Even skeptics admit autonomous exploit chains are a genuine step-change in cybersecurity |
| 💼 **Business Strategy** | Keeps best model internal → competitive advantage while competitors lag |
| ⚠️ **Access Gap** | Glasswing creates two-tier internet: elite companies hardened by AI, everyone else left behind |

### Product Management Implications
- **Security-first MVP** — "Patch later" is dead when AI finds vulns in minutes
- **New PM metrics** — Security posture joins uptime and adoption as core product KPIs
- **Velocity recalibration** — More time on hardening, less on unchecked feature shipping

### AI Developer Implications
- **AI-native security roles** emerging (AI security engineers, threat investigators)
- **Remediation > Discovery** — Vuln finding becomes cheap; patching at scale is the moat
- **Model diversification** — Don't lock into one provider's exclusive access

